A man has been arrested after a member of staff was injured during a burglary at a service station in Guernsey.The staff member was taken to hospital following the incident at Vale Service Station on Tuesaday, between 3:30 BST and 3:45 BST. Guernsey Police arrested a 24-year-old local man on suspicion of aggravated burglary. He remains in custody."Guernsey Police is continuing to appeal to anyone with any information regarding this offence, particularly if you were in the area at the time or have dash cam or CCTV footage," said the force. 
